\meta{description}{Bridge layer connecting plurigrid/ontology to plurigrid/asi. Wires autopoietic ergodicity, Open Games, Gromov-Wasserstein theory, Arena CRDT, Nexus Nodes, and transactive energy into the ASI skill graph for decentralized energy coordination, digital twin multi-agent systems, and grid intelligence.}

\subtree{
\title{Ontology x ASI Interleave}
\p{Bridge connecting \code{\startverb plurigrid/ontology\stopverb} (the Plurigrid protocol's mathematical and systems foundation) to the ASI skill graph.}

\subtree{
\title{plurigrid/ontology -- 7 Core Concepts}
\pre{\startverb
plurigrid/ontology
  1. Autopoietic Ergodicity    -- self-org + time-avg = ensemble-avg convergence
  2. Open Games Framework      -- compositional game theory, Markov categories
  3. Gromov-Wasserstein Theory  -- metric measure space comparison, entropic reg.
  4. Arena System              -- local-first graph DB, Rust + Yrs CRDTs, DuckDB
  5. Digital Twin Architecture -- multi-agent value elicitation, mutual recursion
  6. Nexus Nodes               -- 3-tier hardware: Apple Silicon / RPi4 / Pico W
  7. Transactive Energy        -- stigmergic markets, multi-agent RL + Open Games
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Tripartite Tag}
\p{\code{\startverb arena-crdt(-1) * ontology-asi-interleave(0) * open-games(+1) = 0\stopverb}}

\p{Infrastructure (-1) x Bridge (0) x Strategy (+1) = balanced energy coordination.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Integration Points}
\subtree{
\title{1. Autopoietic Ergodicity to autopoiesis, ergodicity, dynamic-sufficiency}
\p{Ontology defines autopoietic ergodicity as the convergence criterion: a system that self-organizes (autopoiesis) such that time averages equal ensemble averages (ergodicity), minimizing surprise through continuous learning (active inference).}

\pre{\startverb
  ontology                         ASI skills
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
  | autopoietic ergodicity|------->| autopoiesis             |
  |   time-avg = ens-avg  |------->| ergodicity              |
  |   minimize surprise   |------->| dynamic-sufficiency(145)|
  |   embodied gradualism |        | active-inference        |
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
\stopverb}

\p{\code{\startverb dynamic-sufficiency\stopverb} (145 references, central hub) is the primary landing point: it already connects autopoiesis and ergodicity within ASI. Ontology's "embodied gradualism" maps to dynamic-sufficiency's gradual capability accumulation.}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Open Games Framework to open-games, cybernetic-open-game}
\p{The Plurigrid protocol IS a compositional open game. Agents are morphisms in a Markov category with generative (play) and recognition (coplay) channels.}

\pre{\startverb
  ontology                         ASI skills
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
  | Open Games            |------->| open-games              |
  |   Markov categories   |------->| cybernetic-open-game    |
  |   correlated equilib. |------->| equilibrium             |
  |   sense-making / AI   |------->| nashator (9999)         |
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
\stopverb}

\p{Grid = composed game: \code{\startverb node_game @ transmission_game @ market_game\stopverb}. The correlated equilibrium = autopoietically ergodic state = Nash equilibrium that is also thermodynamically stable.}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Gromov-Wasserstein Theory to gflownet, duckdb-spatial}
\p{GW theory compares metric measure spaces and does graph matching across heterogeneous energy networks. Entropic regularization + Bregman projections for efficient optimization.}

\pre{\startverb
  ontology                         ASI skills
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
  | Gromov-Wasserstein    |------->| gflownet (OT sampling)  |
  |   entropic reg.       |------->| duckdb-spatial (graphs) |
  |   Bregman projections |------->| geohash-coloring        |
  |   graph matching      |------->| map-projection          |
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
\stopverb}

\p{GFlowNet samples from energy-proportional distributions over combinatorial structures -- the same optimal transport problem that GW solves for network matching. The entropic regularization in GW parallels the entropy bonus in GFlowNet training.}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Arena CRDT System to crdt, time-travel-crdt, duckdb-ies}
\p{Arena is a local-first graph-based data store in Rust with DuckDB backend and Yrs CRDTs for real-time peer synchronization.}

\pre{\startverb
  ontology                         ASI skills
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
  | Arena System          |        |                         |
  |   Yrs (Y-CRDT)       |------->| crdt                    |
  |   peer sync           |------->| time-travel-crdt        |
  |   DuckDB backend      |------->| duckdb-ies              |
  |   graph store         |------->| duckdb-spatial          |
  |   nodes/edges tables  |------->| duckdb-quadruple-interl.|
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
\stopverb}

\p{Arena schema: \code{\startverb nodes(id, label, properties)\stopverb} + \code{\startverb edges(id, src, dst, label, properties)\stopverb} -- maps directly to DuckDB graph patterns in \code{\startverb duckdb-ies\stopverb} and \code{\startverb duckdb-spatial\stopverb}. The CRDT layer (Yrs) provides exactly the merge semantics that \code{\startverb time-travel-crdt\stopverb} formalizes for ASI skill state.}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Digital Twin Architecture to dynamic-sufficiency, agent-o-rama}
\p{Virtual representations of physical entities. Multi-agent loop in Chat Arena. Agent profiles with value systems and behavior models. Value elicitation via mutual recursion.}

\pre{\startverb
  ontology                         ASI skills
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
  | Digital Twin          |------->| dynamic-sufficiency     |
  |   agent profiles      |------->| agent-o-rama (hub)      |
  |   value elicitation   |------->| cognitive-surrogate     |
  |   active inference    |------->| active-inference        |
  |   mutual recursion    |------->| skill-dispatch          |
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
\stopverb}

\p{The digital twin's active inference loop (predict -> act -> observe -> update) is the same loop that \code{\startverb dynamic-sufficiency\stopverb} implements for ASI skill selection. Each agent twin maintains a GF(3)-colored value system that evolves via CRDT merge with peer twins.}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. Nexus Nodes to hvm-runtime, world-runtime, iot-device-provisioning}
\p{3-tier hardware architecture, all targeting wasm32-unknown-unknown with WASI + capability plugins:}

\pre{\startverb
  Tier          Hardware           Compute        ASI Skill
  +-----------+------------------+-------------+-------------------------+
  | High Power| Apple Silicon    | Full WASM   | hvm-runtime             |
  |           | (M-series Mac)   | + TF ext.   | world-runtime-capability|
  +-----------+------------------+-------------+-------------------------+
  | Low Power | Raspberry Pi 4   | WASI core   | iot-device-provisioning |
  |           | (4GB ARM)        |             |                         |
  +-----------+------------------+-------------+-------------------------+
  | Embedded  | RPi Pico W       | Minimal WASI| iot-device-provisioning |
  |           | (264KB SRAM)     | (sensor hub)|                         |
  +-----------+------------------+-------------+-------------------------+
  Runtime: WasmEdge for high-perf WASM with TensorFlow extensions
\stopverb}

\p{\code{\startverb hvm-runtime\stopverb} handles the high-performance interaction net reduction on Apple Silicon. \code{\startverb world-runtime-capability\stopverb} provides the capability-secure plugin system that maps to WASI capability plugins. \code{\startverb iot-device-provisioning\stopverb} covers the provisioning and attestation workflow for the Low Power and Embedded tiers.}
}

\subtree{
\title{7. Transactive Energy to nashator, open-games, equilibrium}
\p{Market-based transactions between energy grids. Stigmergic feedback for energy availability, demand, and prices. Multi-agent RL + mutual information optimization + Open Games.}

\pre{\startverb
  ontology                         ASI skills
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
  | Transactive Energy    |------->| nashator (market engine) |
  |   stigmergic feedback |------->| open-games (formalism)  |
  |   market clearing     |------->| equilibrium (solver)    |
  |   multi-agent RL      |------->| gym (RL environments)   |
  |   mutual info opt.    |------->| gflownet (sampling)     |
  +-----------------------+        +-------------------------+
\stopverb}

\p{Nashator at 127.0.0.1:9999 is the direct implementation target: each energy node submits bids as open game moves, the Nashator resolves to correlated equilibrium = market clearing price.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Gap Registry}
\p{Capabilities in plurigrid/ontology not yet covered by ASI skills:}

\pre{\startverb
| Ontology Concept | Gap | Priority | Candidate Skill Name |
|-----------------|-----|----------|---------------------|
| Gromov-Wasserstein distance | No dedicated GW/OT skill; gflownet is tangential | HIGH | `gromov-wasserstein` |
| Arena graph store (Rust+Yrs) | No Rust CRDT skill; `crdt` is language-agnostic | MED | `arena-crdt` |
| Stigmergic feedback loops | No stigmergy skill; nashator handles markets only | MED | `stigmergy` |
| WasmEdge runtime | `hvm-runtime` covers HVM, not WasmEdge specifically | LOW | `wasmedge-runtime` |
| Value elicitation protocols | `dynamic-sufficiency` is close but not explicit | LOW | `value-elicitation` |
| Embodied gradualism | Philosophical concept; `autopoiesis` partially covers | LOW | (extend autopoiesis) |
| RPi Pico W sensor hub | `iot-device-provisioning` exists but no Pico W target | LOW | (extend iot-device) |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Plurigrid Protocol Summary}
\p{The Plurigrid protocol = self-rebalancing, self-infrastructuring electricity grid:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Math core}: Open Games + Gromov-Wasserstein + Active Inference}
\li{\strong{Data layer}: Arena (local-first CRDT graph DB, Rust + Yrs + DuckDB)}
\li{\strong{Agent arch}: Digital twins with value elicitation + mutual recursion}
\li{\strong{Equilibrium}: Autopoietically ergodic state = Nash eq. that is thermodynamically stable}
\li{\strong{Energy market}: Stigmergic feedback -> decentralized price discovery -> transactive coordination}
\li{\strong{Hardware}: Nexus Nodes (Apple Silicon / RPi4 / Pico W) all running WASI}
}
}

